The towns of Manchester, Lancaster, Ribchester, Burrow, Elslack and Castleshaw grew around Roman forts. In the centuries after the Roman withdrawal in <a2_0><b5_0><b7_0>410AD<b7_0/><b5_0/><a2_0/> the northern parts of the county probably formed part of the Brythonic kingdom of Rheged, <a3_0>a successor entity to the Brigantes tribe<a3_0/>.
